race.comment: NOR NOR WEST (8) last raced six weeks ago when he quickened impressively to score with plenty in hand over 1018m at Dubbo. Won't find this company any tougher and the slightly longer trip is in his favour. Great chance to chalk up the hat trick. PRESS FORWARD (6) flew home to just win two back over 1000m at Dubbo then again made late ground over the same course and distance last time but was no match for NOR NOR WEST. Needs 1100m now and is rock hard fit. GRINS (3) is back after a four-month spell. Yet to miss the top three in three previous first-up runs. Form at 1100m reads three wins and three minors from eight attempts. It all points to a big run from this genuine mare. LORD OF THE SUN (10) makes life hard by getting back in his races. Turned in another eye-catcher at Tamworth eight days ago. Worth some thought on the quick back-up. The lightly raced ANDALE (7) resumes. Opened last prep with a win over this distance at Wellington. Definite contender.
